ModelAttributeMethodProcessor`.\\n  - Uses a field-level `@DateTimeFormat` annotation so Spring must call `FieldAwareConstructorParameter.getParameterAnnotations()`.\\n  - This reaches the remaining uncovered call site:\\n    - `Class#getDeclaredField(String)` in `FieldAwareConstructorParameter`.\\n\\n- Updated `tests/src/org.springframework/spring-web/5.3.18/build.gradle`\\n  - Added Spring context/test and servlet API test dependencies needed for formatting conversion and mock servlet request support.\\n\\nI did not run or compile tests, per instruction.\", \"textSignature\": \"{\\\"v\\\":1,\\\"id\\\":\\\"msg_0379e235cfb612fb0169fff4a07d088193bb63729df8937069\\\",\\\"phase\\\":\\\"final_answer\\\"}\"}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 664, \"output\": 1160, \"cacheRead\": 37376, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 39200, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"stop\", \"timestamp\": 1778381968029, \"responseId\": \"resp_0379e235cfb612fb0169fff4908a10819380bf4f30e70f50a0\"}}\n[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Evaluating image processing and testing**\\n\\nI’m considering the potential issues with bloating an image, especially since it might exceed limits. Running under Native Image may involve spring-test’s MockHttpServletRequest, which could introduce unnecessary dynamic access. I ponder whether this might impact coverage reports. Creating a custom minimal NativeWebRequest could cut down dependencies. But now I'm questioning whether using an existing public API like `constructAttribute` instead of `resolveArgument` could be more efficient, although it requires certain validations.\\n\\n**Exploring subclassing and method processing**\\n\\nI’m thinking about using a subclass of `ModelAttributeMethodProcessor`, like `TestProcessor`, whic