{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_34","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated new-library generation job failed for `org.springframework:spring-web:5.3.18` and was preserved for manual follow-up: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2185-library-new-request-org.springframework-spring-web-5.3.18-595616b4\n\nThe most likely failing stage was the test-generation/native-image stabilization loop, not coverage collection. Metrics completed successfully and stats reached `21/22` dynamic-access coverage (`95.45%`), but the logs show repeated generated-test failures across 14 iterations. Early on, `gradle-test` failed to compile because Reactor types were missing from the generated test dependencies (`human-intervention-logs/org.springframework:spring-web:5.3.18/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-10T02-35-01-982354Z.log`). Mid-run native tests still contained the scaffold placeholder (`This is just a placeholder, implement your test`) and repeatedly failed in `HandlerMethodTest` with `MissingReflectionRegistrationError` for the synthesized `RequestParam` proxy (`human-intervention-logs/org.springframework:spring-web:5.3.18/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-10T02-59-44-973959Z.log`, `human-intervention-logs/org.springframework:spring-web:5.3.18/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-10T03-08-31-585935Z.log`).\n\nThe native-trace verification loop shows the generator kept uncovering additional native-image registration gaps: missing `META-INF/services/org.slf4j.spi.SLF4JServiceProvider` resource (`human-intervention-logs/org.springframework:spring-web:5.3.18/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-10T02-47-56-355121Z.log`), missing serialization for `org.springframework.remoting.support.RemoteInvocation` (`human-intervention-logs/org.springframework:spring-web:5.3.18/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-10T03-09-42-787341Z.log`), and later `WebDataBinderTest` reflection gaps for generated BeanInfo/Customizer classes (`human-intervention-logs/org.springframework:spring-web:5.3.18/native-test-verify/cycle-7-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-10T03-32-26-827952Z.log`, `human-intervention-logs/org.springframework:spring-web:5.3.18/native-test-verify/cycle-10-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-10T03-33-45-472425Z.log`). The last local targeted run is green (`human-intervention-logs/org.springframework:spring-web:5.3.18/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-10T03-36-05-933004Z.log`), so the preserved branch looks salvageable, but it still needs human review before a PR is opened.\n\n1. Review the preserved branch diff and confirm the final generated tests are library-specific and the metadata stays scoped to `org.springframework:spring-web:5.3.18`.\n2. Re-run the targeted gates for `org.springframework:spring-web:5.3.18` (`checkMetadataFiles` and `test`) to confirm the final green state is reproducible.\n3. If the branch stays green, clean up any leftover generation scaffolding/noise and use the preserved branch as the basis for a manual PR."}}
